 *
 * Each handler decodes registers into typed values, resolves the territory
 * via registry_require(r->r[0], &err), reads the relevant territory_data
 * field, and writes the result back into the register block.
 *
 * Register conventions reproduced from:
 *   TerritoryManager/s/SWIs     (Manager-side SWI veneers)
 *   TerritoryModule/s/Entries   (per-territory entry-point semantics)
 *   TerritoryModule/s/Transform (Territory_TransformString)
 *
 * In the original ABI most of these SWIs (Alphabet, AlphabetIdentifier,
 * SelectKeyboardHandler, WriteDirection, *Table, ReadSymbols,
 * ReadCalendarInformation, TransformString, IME) were dispatched straight
 * through the Manager's CallTerritory to the territory's own entry routine,
 * which returned the value in registers.  In this all-C rewrite the Manager
 * holds the territory as pure data, so we read the field directly.
 */
